reviews.productTitle: Leviton 5243-W 15 Amp, 120/277 Volt, Duplex Style Two 3-Way Combination Switch, Commercial Grade, White
reviews.text: To the point, this product is a space saver. Let's you reduce two 3 way switches, in a 2 gang, down to a 1 gang box. As you are dealing with potentially (9) 12 gauge conductors in a 1 gang box, it stands to reason that there will be tension pushing the switch into place for final fitment. The retaining bracket is riveted once in the rear center, but the top and bottom bindings use a weird plastic retaining clip. As you draw this switch back into final position and compress those conductors, the plate tends to bend and the back rivet and the top and bottom clips retaining the housing pop out of place. Outward no less. In other words, instead of clamping the switch in place, tightening pops the entire switch housing outward, loosening the plastic portion of the switch from the bracket. I was able to use a c-clamp to pinch the top and bottom of the retaining bracket closer to the plastic housing (perhaps a 16th or so) ultimately allowing me to get it set right, but for a premium brand @ a premium price, this was remarkably poorly designed. In my particular install, I had the forethought to use a deep junction box. For a standard box, I do not think proper installation in its intended application would even be possible. If you have any other alternative, i would definitely avoid this product. Best of luck.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on April 27, 2025
reviews.title: I would avoid this item if you have any alternative

reviews.text: My parents house was built in the late 1970s and they have a hanging light above a landing in a raised ranch house. This switch is what is on that landing next to the porch light switch. It controls the hanging light, and a downstairs hallway light. Each light I mentioned is also controlled by at least 1 other switch (downstairs hallway is controlled by 2). I searched everywhere for a double 3-way switch, and Amazon was the only place that had this. Instructions are kinda hard to understand, but not impossible. There is a metal tab that's on the switch by default that needs to be broken off to separate the switches. I used the old switch as a reference to wiring up the new one.

reviews.title: 3-way combo switch x 2

I didn't even know half switches existed until I started looking around, and when I needed 3-way versions, I found this singular option.
